The paper discusses the mechanism and effects of web censorship in Pakistan, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The study also involves analyzing the accessibility of websites from multiple networks, which can be categorized under cybercrime (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses methods of bypassing restrictions, which can be categorized under performance (cs.PF).
